---
Kowloon's Black Ledger documents the catastrophe's northern effects: route disruption, supply chain collapse, and mass displacement along the oasis corridor.
The Neon Covenant's crisis protocol framework was partly developed in response to the catastrophe's aftermath: multi-city coordination failures during recovery became the design failures the Covenant was built to avoid.
When the Solar Court and Moon Sovereign traditions were simultaneously discredited, every oasis settlement had to negotiate local authority from scratch; that negotiation took three generations.
The catastrophe demonstrated what happens when competing institutional authorities attempt to merge through ritual rather than negotiation: institutional vacuum and Fracture Era fragmentation.
Kowloon's lesson: institutional authority must be built through documented covenant, not inherited from divine claims or merged through ritual.
The Neon Covenant's name references this lesson: it is a covenant, negotiated and documented, not a rite attempted and catastrophic.

