Khenari descent-records across nine cycles document the catastrophe's mortuary consequences as the largest event of unrecorded death in corridor history.
Mass death in the thermal zone occurred faster than any mortuary institution could process; bodies were consumed, records destroyed, lineages severed.
Nine cycles of descent-record review have not closed this debt because the missing persons cannot be identified without the destroyed records.
Khenari in Kiess's witness registry filed a formal notation: the Ninth Meridian represents a gap in the corridor's legal death-record constituting an ongoing administrative emergency.
The notation has been acknowledged but not acted upon; no institution has authority to close mortuary records for deaths that predate the current governance framework.
Khenari position: the responsible party, the Solar Court, no longer exists to remedy it. Kiess's three-power charter has no mechanism for assigning liability to defunct institutions.
Each Khenari descent-cycle, elders review the Ninth Meridian notation. It has not closed in nine cycles. They do not expect it to close in the tenth.
